des: The Omak-Okanogan County Chronicle serves North-Central Washington's Okanogan County. The weekly newspaper also covers Ferry County and part of Douglas County. The newspaper also produces a joint weekend publication with The Wenatchee World. The newspaper is owned by Eagle Newspapers, Inc. Teresa Myers has served as the publisher and advertising manager since Oct. 1, 2015.
